Data Intelligence Analyst
As a Data Intelligence Analyst, you can make a difference by creating value out of data-driven innovations that result in actionable insights to help drive the Compliance function.
Do you have experience in a similar role and are you excited about performing in-depth and reproducible data analyses, and/or validating data by combining and interpreting external and internal quantitative and qualitative data? Then this could be your next role. Please apply for this job in Utrecht.
You and your job
On a day-to-day basis, you will have a variety of tasks including analysing the needs of the Compliance department and translating the needs into solutions. You will collect, analyse and turn data into actionable insights, with the aim of providing timely and complete information to contribute to decision-making.
Your top 3 responsibilities
Align with compliance colleagues on the information needs;
Perform in-depth and reproducible data analyses, and/or validate data by combining and interpreting external and internal quantitative and qualitative data;
Develop and maintain analytics solutions and advise the Compliance colleagues on how to use data analytics to create actionable insights.
Example Projects/Activites:
Develop and maintain Power BI dashboards for compliance-related reporting and analytics, such as tracking and reporting on customer transactions to detect potential money laundering activities.
Generate compliance-related reports and visualizations using Power BI, such as analyzing and presenting data on customer complaints to identify trends and potential areas for improvement in compliance processes.
Collaborate with cross-functional teams, such as IT and risk management, to ensure data accuracy and compliance with relevant laws and regulations in the development and maintenance of Power BI dashboards.
Facts and Figures
36-40 hours per week;
Location Utrecht;
Worldwide 43.822 Rabobank-collega’s;
The team itself
As a Data Business Engineer Compliance, you will be part of the Risk & Data team, which is one of the 4 teams of the Monitoring, Validation, Risk, and Data department within the Compliance department of Rabobank Group. As one of the most dynamic departments of the bank, compliance has a key role in the promotion and safeguarding of the integrity as well as the reputation of Rabobank Group. Compliance promotes and monitors that the integrity and compliance rules are closely adhered to through its teams dedicated to business line compliance for the various markets (e.g., Retail Netherlands, Rural & Retail, Wholesale, Member Banks), as well as the expertise centre on themes such as market abuse, conflicts of interests and financial economic crime.
Together we achieve more than alone
We believe in the power of difference. Bringing together people's differences is what makes us an even better bank. So we are very curious about what you can bring to our team at Risk &Data.
“In the compliance and fraud domain, you will work with advanced machine learning and AI to find the special and investigated cases. This world is always in motion, every day brings new challenge.”
Jan Veldsink, Artificial Intelligence Officer Compliance
The 20-25 people in MVRD drive data-driven compliance and are responsible for the setup of an agile data-driven compliance organization including the risk and data expertise in the compliance department. Working together is the way we work; as 1 effective/purposeful/data-minded /expert team at Rabobank. Talking of Rabobank: We are a Dutch bank that operates in 38 countries for over 9,5000,000 customers. Together with these customers, our members, and partners we stand side by side to create a world in which everyone has access to enough healthy food. In the Netherlands, we work to create a country in which people are happy with how they live, work and do business.
You and your talent
Bachelor or masters or equivalent experience in a field such as Informatica or Business Analytics;
Experience in data analysis and data driven solutions;
Professional experience using Power BI and similar tools to communicate insights and drive data-driven decision making;
Design and visualization skills to create clear and effective data visualizations for dashboards and reports;
Familiarity with data integration and data preparation processes to ensure accurate data is displayed in dashboards;
Collaborative experience with machine learning or software engineering teams;
Experience with Agile philosophies;
Great communication skills in English (minimum B2 or C1 level);
Affinity with Compliance themes such as Financial and Economic Crime, Fraud and Privacy;
As a Data Business Engineer, you have developed the following competencies:
Great team player and in possession of a results-oriented attitude;
Proficiency in problem-solving and a self-starter;
Customer-oriented and collaborating;
Result driven with good judgment and decision-making skills;
Taking ownership.
This is what we offer you
A base salary up to €6.741,- gross per month in scale 9 or 10. Salary will be set by comparing experience levels with our internal workforce;
€ 750,00 budget to set up your home workplace and up to € 40,00 for working from home allowance per month;
Thirteenth month's salary and 8% holiday allowance;
An Employee Benefit Budget (EBB) of 11% of your gross salary to be used at your discretion. Buy extra holiday hours, add more to your pension savings or ask for part of the extra budget to be paid out;
Flexible working times and hybrid location-independent working within the limits dictated by working in a team;
100% reimbursement of commuting costs if you travel by public transport;
A pension scheme to which you contribute 5.5%;
An inspiring international working environment with enthusiastic professionals.
A culture that is characterized by entrepreneurship, personal development, and ambition.
This is a selection of the terms of employment for a Data Business Engineer Compliance on a 36-hour working week. You can find all terms of employment on https://rabobank.jobs/en/conditions-of-employment.
If you have questions about the job content, then please contact Minke Visser, Team Lead Risk & Data via minke.visser01@rabobank.nl or 06- 255 471 20;
For your questions about the recruitment process in general, please contact Rose Osté, Corporate Recruiter, via rose.oste@rabobank.nl
The application process includes screening. Based on the screening procedures in place at Rabobank, we assess whether new staff are reliable enough to work at Rabobank;
Your privacy is important to us. Do you want to know more, click on this link;
Rabobank believes that having a diverse workforce helps make us a better bank. When we put teams together, we strive to create a diverse balance of people in terms of gender, background, culture, age, preferences, and skills. At Rabobank, everyone can be themselves. Read more about Diversity & Inclusion here.
We look forward to your application!

The opportunity & the team
You will work within the vertical Data Protection Compliance, a new department within Compliance that is installed per March 2023. Data Protection is an important risk area with growing interest from both internal and external stakeholders.
As a Global Delegated Data Protection Officer, you are focused on managing, advising and challenging risks related to the individual/data subject arising from processing of personal data by ING. Personal Data Protection is a key compliance risk that the bank needs to manage.
As a Global Delegated Data Protection Officer, you are a member of the Global Data Protection Advisory & Policy team that ensures quality on advice & challenge of each processing of personal data with global (i.e., covering more than one country) impact.
The Global Data Protection Policy & Advisory team forms with the Data Protection Risk Management team the vertical Data Protection Compliance.
Roles and responsibilities
As a Global Delegated Data Protection Officer
You provide advice on requests of the Business and challenge their personal data processing via instruments like LIA, DPIA, and TIA within the global scope of the Data Protection Compliance vertical, which means personal data processing covering global/multi country activities and solutions. You participate in global programs to help first line of defense to be compliant with data protection laws and regulations. You also advice and challenge on data retention obligations;
You coordinate global data breach events and for reporting and follow up on this towards the Local DPO’s and for reporting to the Lead Supervisory Authority, if applicable;
You contribute to communicating a consistent approach and interpretation of GPDP (Global Personal Data Protection, our internal policy) and GDPP (Global Data Protection Policy; our binding corporate rules) via the DPO community;
You will support final decision making on specific files and in monitoring that solutions (agreed upon with the business) are implemented;
You will support the Global Lead DP Policy & Advisory in communication with the Data Protection Authority and other stakeholders;
You prepare training & awareness on data protection and data retention topics, and specific topics like ethics and artificial intelligence;
You will have a focus on specific geographical areas such as Market Leaders or Retail/rest of the world.
How to succeed
We hire smart people like you for your potential. Our biggest expectation is that you’ll stay curious. Keep learning. Take on responsibility. In return, we’ll back you to develop into an even more awesome version of yourself.
Key competencies
You have (global) stakeholder management and influencing skills;
You can work in a multidisciplinary setting;
You can work independently, think and act out of the box and take responsibility;
You are a team player, you trust others and can be trusted;
Furthermore, you adhere to the ING orange code values and it is evident for you that your behavior is fully aligned with these values. You are also prepared to take the Banker’s Oath.
Your technical skills and track record
You have professional experience with Data Protection activities or related legal experience preferably in a banking environment and you are familiar with security and IT ecosystems;
You have in depth knowledge on GDPR regulation and, preferably, related internal ING policies;
You have excellent collaboration skills and ability to work across functional and geographic lines;
You have a university degree, preferably in Law, or equivalent knowledge/experience;
You are excellent in English (verbal/written) and have good communication skills.
Reports to Global Lead Data Protection Policy and Advisory
Location: Amsterdam, Netherlands
Rewards and benefits
We want to make sure that it’s possible for you to strike the right balance between your career and your private life. You can find out more about our employment conditions at https://www.ing.jobs/netherlands/Why-ING/benefits.htm
The benefits of working with us at ING include:
A salary tailored to your qualities and experience
24-27 vacation days depending on contract
Pension scheme
13th month salary
Individual Savings Contribution (BIS), 3.5% of your gross annual salary
8% Holiday payment
Personal growth and challenging work with endless possibilities
An informal working environment with innovative colleagues
Work Agile, so new ideas come to life faster
About us
With 57,000 employees and operations in approximately 40 countries, there is no shortage of opportunities for people with initiative who want to help people take a step ahead in life and in business. Do you want to work at the cutting edge of what’s possible and at the same time ensure you work with integrity and hold the customer’s interests at heart? Do you want to be surrounded by progressive, inspiring, diverse and supportive colleagues? Then there is no better place to invest your talents than at ING. Join us. Apply today.

Het transformeren van de manier waarop organisaties risico's aanpakken door het leveren van innovatief denken en verantwoorde inzichten uit data en technologie. Bij Deloitte.
What impact will you make?
Als Junior Manager Data & Responsible Insight speel je een leidende rol in de veelzijdige dataprogramma's van onze klanten. Daarbij ben je een sparringpartner voor de data-uitdagingen waar onze klanten voor staan. Je neemt verantwoordelijkheid binnen het (project)team door consultants aan te sturen in hun dagelijkse werkzaamheden. Daarnaast als Junior Manager Data & Responsible Insight stuur je de datatransformatie van onze klanten aan. Met jouw ervaring in het datadomein begrijp je zowel het business- als het technische perspectief. Je herkent de waarde van data voor duurzaamheid en bent altijd op zoek naar manieren om dit potentieel te benutten. Samen met je collega's werk je aan het opzetten en verfijnen van robuuste datapijplijnen. Dit alles met het doel om ervoor te zorgen dat data betrouwbaar is, en makkelijk te gebruiken en te onderhouden.
Je interesse al gewekt? Mooi, want wij doen epic stuff met responsible data! We maken een tastbare impact door onze klanten te helpen hun data te organiseren en geavanceerde verantwoorde inzichten te bieden. Als Junior Manager speel je een centrale rol in de veelzijdige dataprogramma's van onze klanten. Daarbij ben je een sparringpartner voor de data-uitdagingen waar onze klanten voor staan. Je neemt verantwoordelijkheid binnen het (project)team door begeleiding te geven aan junior/senior consultants in hun dagelijkse werkzaamheden.
How do you do this?
Verantwoordelijk zijn voor de kwaliteit van je eigen werk en dat van andere consultants;
Het opzetten en verbeteren van datapijplijnen met ingebouwde auditing-, logging- en validatiemechanismen om de datakwaliteit te waarborgen;
Complexe gegevensvereisten vertalen in analytische modellen;
Data engineering gebruiken om grote datasets voor te bereiden voor analytics;
Het uitvoeren van technische analyses met behulp van state-of-the-art technieken op grote datasets;
Het uitleggen van inzichten die we uit duurzaamheidsdata halen;
Het adviseren van klanten over hoe geavanceerde data-analysetechnieken kunnen helpen bij het beheersen van duurzaamheidsrisico's;
Het voorbereiden en faciliteren van vergaderingen, presentaties en workshops met klanten;
Rapporteren over projecten aan de klant en collega's op de hoogte houden;
De leiding nemen in de ontwikkeling van ons interne team, door bij te dragen aan werving, te werken aan maatschappelijke impact projecten of proof of concepts te ontwikkelen.
What’s in it for you?
Je deelt bij ons mee in de winst. Boven op een vast salaris.
Altijd blijven groeien. Met ons development program.
Vergoeding om je thuiswerkplek op een ergonomisch verantwoorde manier in te richten én een internetvergoeding.
Parttime (32 uur) of fulltime (40 uur) werken.
Flexibele werktijden, je deelt je eigen agenda in.
26 vakantiedagen per jaar bij een fulltime dienstverband en de mogelijkheid om extra dagen in te kopen.
Ruil 3 nationale feestdagen voor 3 niet-nationale feestdagen. Als je wilt.
Een goede mobiliteitsregeling: de keuze uit verschillende opties zoals een leaseauto, reizen met het OV, een cash budget of een combinatie daarvan.
Een laptop en iPhone. Ook voor privégebruik.
Een pensioenregeling waarbij je eigen bijdrage slechts 2% is. Voor later.
Mogelijkheid om deel te nemen aan de collectieve ziektekostenregeling.
Fiscaal voordelige zaken. Denk aan bedrijfsfitness, het aanschaffen van een fiets tegen bruto salaris of de mogelijkheid om een fiets te leasen.
De mogelijkheid om gebruik te maken van 55 uur oppasdienst per kalenderjaar, als jouw kind 12 jaar of jonger is.
Een maandelijks budget waarmee je keuzes kunt maken in flexibele arbeidsvoorwaarden zoals extra vakantiedagen of het financieren van een fietsplan.
Zes weken volledig betaald geboorteverlof voor traditionele huishoudens en regenbooggezinnen.
Be the true you
Ben je enthousiast over de bovenstaande functieomschrijving? Dan maken wij graag kennis met jou! Voor de rol van Junior Manager Data & Responsible Insight beschik je daarnaast over:
Een kwantitatief georiënteerde hbo- of wo-opleiding, zoals Econometrie, Informatica, Wiskunde, Business Analytics, Artificial Intelligence of Data Science;
Minimaal 4 jaar relevante ervaring in een commerciële omgeving of een PhD in een relevant vakgebied;
Affiniteit met programmeren in SQL en/of Python;
Kennis die een passende mix van analytisch, IT en - financiële - data omvat;
Eigenschappen als analytisch, zelfstandig en kritisch zijn voor jou vanzelfsprekend;
Uitstekende beheersing van de Engelse taal in woord en geschrift (Nederlands is geen must, maar wel een grote pré).
(W)here
Jouw expertise deel je met zo'n 75 andere collega's in het Data & Responsible Insight-team dat onderdeel is van Deloitte Risk Advisory. Ons team ondersteunt onze klanten bij het transformeren van hun risico’s, door innovatief te denken en inzichten en vooruitzichten te halen uit data en technologie. Wij helpen organisaties met het transformeren naar een op inzicht gedreven organisatie die snel in kan spelen op ontwikkelingen.
Binnen deze afdeling vinden we het belangrijk om jezelf continu te ontwikkelen. Daarom hechten we veel waarde aan innovatie en persoonlijke ontwikkeling.
Bij Deloitte werken we hybride. We combineren werken vanuit huis, bij de klant en op kantoor zo optimaal mogelijk.
Let's make impact. Apply now!
Bij Deloitte staan we open voor alle mensen die kwaliteit en ambitie meebrengen. We zijn dan ook benieuwd wie jíj bent.

